154 §41-27A-3
155 (a) The Alabama Geographic Information Program Office
156 (GIS Office) is established to be the operating arm of the
157 Executive Council. Except as provided in Section 41-27A-5, the
158 GIS Office shall be the sole instrumentality of the state for
159 coordination of geographic information, GIS, and other
160 geospatial-related technologies by all state departments and
161 agencies or state-funded entities.
162 (b) The GIS Office shall be a division in the Alabama
163 State Law Enforcement Agency (ALEA), which shall provide
164 administrative services for the GIS office.
165 (c)(1) The GIS Office shall be managed by a director,
166 who shall be the Geographic Information Officer (GIO), who
167 shall be appointed by and serve at the pleasure of the
168 Governor.
Page 6

Governor.
HB97 INTRODUCED
169 (2) The GIO shall be assisted by a deputy, who shall be
170 appointed by and serve at the pleasure of the Governor.
171 (3) The GIO shall manage the GIS Office subject to the
172 policies, standards, guidance, and instruction of the
173 Executive Council.
174 (d) The GIS Office shall identify, plan, and implement
175 the most efficient and effective means to use and integrate
176 geographic information as a strategic management resource, to
177 include all of the following duties:
178 (1) Identify duplicative geospatial acquisitions,
179 initiatives, and operations across state government and
180 recommend efforts to minimize duplication of such activities.
181 (2) Maintain a master index of all geographic
182 information maintained by any political subdivision of the
183 state or other state-funded entity.
184 (3) Maintain a central repository and data services for
185 the storage of, or access to, any geographic information that
186 may be lawfully used for state or for local government
187 geospatial-related operations or for any lawful private sector
188 activity.
189 (4) Assist government operations with implementation of
190 state geospatial standards as adopted by the Executive
191 Council.
192 (5) Through ALEA, coordinate procurements, pool funds,
193 negotiate and enter into contracts or memoranda of
194 understanding in furtherance of GIS Office duties.
195 (6) Provide administrative and technical support to the
196 Executive Council.
