237 §41-27A-5
238 (a) In aid of the role and duties of the GIS Office as
239 the statewide coordinator and central repository for
240 geographic information pursuant to Section 41-27A-3, the 911
241 Board is recognized as the sole authority for the gathering,
242 remediation, and maintenance of geographic information for the
243 provision of emergency 911 services to the residents of
244 Alabama, pursuant to Section 11-98-4.1.
245 (b) The 911 Board shall regularly inform the Executive
246 Council and the GIO on its GIS data gathering and remediation
247 activities, GIS auditing and monitoring protocols, and
248 operational policies to ensure the utmost coordination between
249 the GIS Office and the 911 Board in similar or parallel tasks
250 and responsibilities to avoid duplication and enhance
251 uniformity in protocols, standards, data gathering,
252 maintenance, and storage wherever possible and efficient.
Page 9

maintenance, and storage wherever possible and efficient.
